<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FFA1FFDD39D309D647DEB8A5" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FFA1FFDD39D309D647DEB8A5" blockId="47.[136,1452,736,978]" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">
The original description of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA1FFDD38E609D6442AB9D5" authorityName="Kleinhoonte" authorityYear="1926" box="[445,772,736,762]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flammatum">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA1FFDD38E609D6442AB9D5" box="[445,772,736,762]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">Stryphnodendron flammatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a fragment of a compound leaf and lists general characteristics of the 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA1FFDD382F08324521B831" box="[372,527,772,798]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="family">Leguminosae</taxonomicName>
. This vague description and the vegetative 
<typeStatus id="7C4B50F0FFA1FFDD3AB708334332B830" box="[1004,1052,773,799]" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">type</typeStatus>
specimens preclude the recognition of this taxon as any existing species of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA1FFDD3B13081E4427B86D" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1837" box="[584,777,808,834]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="91843240FFA1FFDD3B13081E4427B86D" box="[584,777,808,834]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">Stryphnodendron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or as any genus of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FFA1FFDD3AA9081E4373B86D" box="[1010,1117,808,834]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
, since the specimens lack the apical bud with the characteristic indumentum and prefoliation, and the extrafloral nectaries of the petioles, rachis or rachillae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FFA1FFDD39E608A347EEB8FD" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" type="description">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FFA1FFDD39E608A347EEB8FD" blockId="47.[136,1452,736,978]" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">
We found several duplicates of the 
<typeStatus id="7C4B50F0FFA1FFDD3B6608A34543B880" box="[573,621,917,943]" pageId="47" pageNumber="274">type</typeStatus>
indicated by 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FFA1FFDD3A5B08A244F2B880" author="Kleinhoonte, A." box="[768,988,916,943]" pageId="47" pageNumber="274" pagination="391 - 417" refId="ref42664" refString="Kleinhoonte, A. (1926) Leguminosae. In: Pulle, A., Neue Beitrage zur Flora Suriname IV. Recueil des Travaux Botaniques Neerlandais 22: 391 - 417." type="journal article" year="1926">Kleinhoonte (1926)</bibRefCitation>
, requiring the lectotypification performed here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
